        used for plants here called Pluchea carolinensis. The taxon was long identified as P.
        odorata (R. K. Godfrey 1952) and was known as P. [Conyza] symphytifolia (Miller) Gillis for
        a while. Conyza symphytifolia Miller is a synonym of Neurolaena lobata (Linnaeus) Cassini
